        </nav>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="govuk-grid-row govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Return of property</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Sometimes property is kept as evidence by the police for the investigation. You are able to have property returned, usually at the conclusion of the case.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Speak to the Police Officer In Charge via the police website, 101, or email address, and you will be asked to bring ID to your local police station to retrieve it.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        If the defendant appeals conviction then the property might need to be kept.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        For further information speak to your local police.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
